# AgP Playground Design System

This document outlines the design system for the AgP Playground, including color palettes, typography, and usage guidelines.

## Component Primitives Philosophy

**Always prefer using existing component primitives over creating custom inline styles.**

### Core Principles

1. **Use Available Components First**
   - Before writing custom button, input, or UI element styles, check if a component exists in `components/ui/`
   - Leverage existing component variants (e.g., `Button` with `variant="ghost"`, `variant="outline"`, etc.)
   - This ensures consistency, accessibility, and maintainability

2. **When to Add New Variants**
   - Only add new variants to existing components when there's a clear, reusable pattern
   - New variants should be added to the base component file, not inline
   - Ensure the new variant follows the existing design system principles
   - Document the new variant with examples

3. **When NOT to Add New Variants**
   - For one-off styling needs, use composition with existing variants
   - Don't create variants that break the design system (e.g., brand colors for general buttons)
   - Avoid variants that are too specific to a single use case

### Available Component Primitives

- **Button**: `components/ui/button.tsx`
  - Variants: `default`, `destructive`, `outline`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `link`
  - Sizes: `default`, `sm`, `lg`, `icon`
  
- **Select**: `components/ui/select.tsx`
  - Full dropdown component with trigger, content, and item primitives

- **Icons**: `components/icons/`
  - 160+ pre-built icons, use these instead of inline SVGs

### Examples

**✅ Good - Using Component Primitives:**
```tsx
// Using Button component with variants
<Button variant="ghost" size="sm" onClick={handleSave}>
  <DownloadIcon className="w-4 h-4" />
  Save
</Button>

// Using existing icon component
import { CheckIcon } from '@/components/icons';
<CheckIcon className="w-4 h-4 text-gray-6" />
```

**❌ Bad - Custom Inline Styles:**
```tsx
// Don't create custom button styles inline
<button className="px-3 py-1.5 bg-gray-8 text-gray-1 rounded hover:bg-gray-7">
  Save
</button>

// Don't use inline SVG when icon exists
<svg className="w-4 h-4">...</svg>
```

**✅ Good - Adding a New Variant:**
```tsx
// In components/ui/button.tsx, add to variants object
variants: {
  variant: {
    default: '...',
    outline: '...',
    subtle: 'bg-gray-2 text-gray-7 hover:bg-gray-3', // New reusable variant
  }
}
```

**❌ Bad - Over-Specific Variant:**
```tsx
// Don't add variants that are too specific
variants: {
  variant: {
    saveButtonInHeaderOnly: '...',  // Too specific!
  }
}
```

## Color System

### Primary Grayscale Palette (Preferred)

**Always use grayscale colors for UI components.** This ensures consistency across light and dark themes.

#### Light Mode
- `bg-gray-1` / `text-gray-1`: `#ffffff` - Pure white, primary background
- `bg-gray-2` / `text-gray-2`: `#f7f7f8` - Canvas background (main page background)
- `bg-gray-3` / `text-gray-3`: `#ececee` - Subtle backgrounds, hover states
- `bg-gray-4` / `text-gray-4`: `#dcdcdf` - Borders, dividers
- `bg-gray-5` / `text-gray-5`: `#ccccd1` - Disabled states
- `bg-gray-6` / `text-gray-6`: `#6b6b70` - Secondary text, muted content
- `bg-gray-7` / `text-gray-7`: `#3e3e3f` - Primary interactive text
- `bg-gray-8` / `text-gray-8`: `#1d1d1f` - Headings, high-emphasis text

#### Dark Mode
- `bg-gray-1` / `text-gray-1`: `#1f1f23` - Primary background
- `bg-gray-2` / `text-gray-2`: `#2b2d31` - Canvas background
- `bg-gray-3` / `text-gray-3`: `#38383d` - Subtle backgrounds, hover states
- `bg-gray-4` / `text-gray-4`: `#47474d` - Borders, dividers
- `bg-gray-5` / `text-gray-5`: `#56565d` - Disabled states
- `bg-gray-6` / `text-gray-6`: `#a9a9ad` - Secondary text, muted content
- `bg-gray-7` / `text-gray-7`: `#d2d2d5` - Primary interactive text
- `bg-gray-8` / `text-gray-8`: `#f2f2f3` - Headings, high-emphasis text

### Special Background Colors

- `bg-canvas-background`: Main application background
  - Light: `#f7f7f8`
  - Dark: `#18181b`
- `bg-card-background`: Card/modal backgrounds
  - Light: `#ffffff`
  - Dark: `#1f1f23`

### Brand Colors

Use sparingly and only for brand-specific elements:

- `bg-h-red` / `text-h-red`: `#ff4800` - H Company red
- `bg-h-green` / `text-h-green`: `#10c56d` - H Company green

**Note:** Avoid using brand colors for general UI. Prefer grayscale.

### Semantic Color Palettes

Each color has an 8-step scale (1-8), where:
- **1-3**: Light backgrounds, subtle states
- **4-5**: Medium backgrounds, borders
- **6**: Primary color, main interactive elements
- **7-8**: Dark text, high contrast

Available palettes: `amber`, `blue`, `green`, `magenta`, `orange`, `pink`, `purple`, `red`

Usage: `bg-{color}-{scale}` or `text-{color}-{scale}`

Example: `bg-blue-6`, `text-red-7`

**Use semantic colors only when meaning is critical** (e.g., error states, success indicators).

## Color Usage Guidelines

### ✅ Do
- Use grayscale colors for all standard UI elements
- Use `text-gray-8` for headings and high-emphasis content
- Use `text-gray-6` for secondary/muted text
- Use `text-gray-7` for interactive elements
- Use `bg-gray-1` for cards and containers
- Use `bg-gray-2` or `bg-canvas-background` for main page backgrounds
- Use `bg-gray-3` for hover states
- Use `border-gray-4` for borders and dividers
- Let Tailwind's `dark:` prefix handle theme switching automatically

### ❌ Don't
- Don't use brand colors (`h-red`, `h-green`) for general UI elements
- Don't use semantic colors (blue, green, red, etc.) unless conveying specific meaning
- Don't hardcode colors with hex values or oklch values
- Don't use `text-primary` or `bg-primary` (these are shadcn defaults, prefer grayscale)
- Don't mix color systems (stick to grayscale)

### Examples

**Good:**
```tsx
// Card with proper grayscale usage
<div className="bg-gray-1 border border-gray-4 rounded-lg shadow p-6">
  <h2 className="text-24-medium-heading text-gray-8">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-14-regular-body text-gray-6">Description</p>
  <button className="bg-gray-8 text-gray-1 hover:bg-gray-7">
    Action
  </button>
</div>

// Theme-aware icon
<CheckIcon className="w-4 h-4 text-gray-6" />

// Status indicator with semantic color
<span className="text-12-medium-body bg-gray-7 text-gray-1">
  Completed
</span>
```

**Bad:**
```tsx
// Don't use brand colors for general buttons
<button className="bg-h-green text-white">Submit</button>

// Don't use semantic colors without meaning
<div className="bg-blue-3 text-blue-8">Generic Card</div>

// Don't use shadcn defaults
<span className="text-primary">Text</span>

// Don't hardcode colors
<div style={{ color: '#3e3e3f' }}>Text</div>
```

## Typography System

All typography classes follow the pattern: `text-{size}-{weight}-{type}`

### Font Families
- **Inter**: Primary body text (400-900 weights)
- **InterDisplay**: Headings and large text (100-900 weights)
- **GeistMono**: Code and monospace text (100-900 weights)

### Available Typography Classes

#### Body Text
- `text-9-regular-body`: 9px / 400 / 12px line-height
- `text-14-regular-body`: 14px / 400 / 20px line-height (most common)
- `text-14-medium-body`: 14px / 500 / 20px line-height
- `text-16-regular-body`: 16px / 400 / 24px line-height
- `text-16-medium-body`: 16px / 500 / 24px line-height
- `text-24-regular-body`: 24px / 400 / 32px line-height
- `text-24-medium-body`: 24px / 500 / 32px line-height

#### Headings
- `text-12-regular-heading`: 12px / 400 / 12px line-height
- `text-12-medium-heading`: 12px / 500 / 12px line-height
- `text-14-regular-heading`: 14px / 400 / 16px line-height
- `text-14-medium-heading`: 14px / 500 / 16px line-height
- `text-16-regular-heading`: 16px / 400 / 20px line-height
- `text-16-medium-heading`: 16px / 500 / 20px line-height (section headings)
- `text-18-bold-heading`: 18px / 700 / 20px line-height
- `text-24-regular-heading`: 24px / 400 / 28px line-height
- `text-24-medium-heading`: 24px / 500 / 28px line-height
- `text-24-bold-heading`: 24px / 700 / 28px line-height (page titles)
- `text-32-light-heading`: 32px / 300 / 28px line-height
- `text-36-light-heading`: 36px / 300 / 40px line-height
- `text-36-bold-heading`: 36px / 700 / 40px line-height
- `text-64-light-heading`: 64px / 200 / 72px line-height

#### Monospace
- `text-10-mono-medium-heading`: 10px / 500 / 12px line-height
- `text-13-mono-regular-heading`: 13px / 400 / 16px line-height
- `text-13-mono-regular-body`: 13px / 400 / 20px line-height
- `text-13-mono-medium-heading`: 13px / 500 / 16px line-height
- `text-13-mono-medium-body`: 13px / 500 / 20px line-height

### Typography Usage Guidelines

#### ✅ Do
- Use `text-24-bold-heading` for page titles
- Use `text-24-medium-heading` for main section headings
- Use `text-16-medium-heading` for subsection headings
- Use `text-14-regular-body` for standard body text
- Use `text-14-medium-body` for emphasized body text
- Use `text-12-regular-heading` for labels and small headings
- Combine typography classes with color classes: `text-24-bold-heading text-gray-8`

#### ❌ Don't
- Don't use raw Tailwind text size classes (`text-sm`, `text-base`, etc.)
- Don't use raw font-weight classes (`font-medium`, `font-bold`, etc.)
- Don't manually set font-family, use the provided typography classes
- Don't override line-height or letter-spacing defined in typography classes

