## Theme Support

All colors automatically support dark mode through Tailwind's `dark:` variant. The design system is configured to handle theme switching automatically through CSS variables.

### Best Practices
- Define colors using the grayscale palette
- Let the design system handle theme switching automatically
- Use `dark:` variants only for special cases where automatic switching doesn't work

### Example
```tsx
// Automatic theme switching (preferred)
<div className="bg-gray-1 text-gray-8">Content</div>

// Manual dark mode override (use sparingly)
<div className="bg-gray-1 dark:bg-gray-2 text-gray-8">Content</div>
```

